full_text: A policy change transaction is used to modify the policy while it is in force. Policy changes usually have an impact on the premium. For example, one months into the policy period, the insured calls to remove a vehicle from the commercial auto policy. Locate the policy and open the policy file. Click Actions. Select Change Policy. Enter the effective date in a description. The effective date here is a when the changes are effective, not the start date of the policy term. It must be within the policy term boundary. Click Next to start the policy change transaction. Go to Vehicles. Select the vehicle. Click Remove Vehicle. Click Quote. Since the number of vehicles does not exceed the threshold of asynchronous quoting, it will rate the policy immediately. You can edit the effective date of an unbound policy change by clicking Actions. Select Effective Date under Edit. Click OK to proceed as it may affect premium. Change the effective date. Click Next to go back to the policy change transaction. Click Quote again. Go to Policy Review screen. Go to Policy Review screen. The Differences tab displays the changes comparing to the existing policy. Click the Policy Review tab. The Policy Change Wizard buttons are similar as a submission. If the policy holder is satisfied, you can bind and issue the policy. Click OK to confirm. Filogy of the Differences tab. Filogy of the Differences tab. Filogy of the Differences tab.
